"{\"uid\": \"tomsguide.com-ai-googles-gemini-olympics-ad-is-the-very-worst-way-to-sell-ai-heres-why\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Join the Tom's Guide Club for quick access.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 43, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Tom's Guide Club\", \"from\": 5, \"to\": 25}, {\"ngram\": \"quick access\", \"from\": 30, \"to\": 42}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Enter your email below and we will send confirmation, and sign you up to our newsletter.\", \"from\": 44, \"to\": 132, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"your email\", \"from\": 50, \"to\": 60}, {\"ngram\": \"confirmation\", \"from\": 84, \"to\": 96}, {\"ngram\": \"our newsletter\", \"from\": 117, \"to\": 131}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By submitting your information, you confirm you are aged 16 or over, have read ourPrivacy Policyand agree to theTerms & Conditions.\", \"from\": 134, \"to\": 265, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"your information\", \"from\": 148, \"to\": 164}, {\"ngram\": \"ourPrivacy Policyand\", \"from\": 213, \"to\": 233}, {\"ngram\": \"theTerms\", \"from\": 243, \"to\": 251}, {\"ngram\": \"Conditions\", \"from\": 254, \"to\": 264}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Geographical rules apply.\", \"from\": 266, \"to\": 291, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Geographical rules\", \"from\": 266, \"to\": 284}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An Olympic-sized fail from Google When you purchase through links on our site, we may earn an affiliate commission.Here's how it works.\", \"from\": 293, \"to\": 429, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 320, \"end\": 326, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.4285481808935853e-16, \"text\": \"Google\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"An Olympic-sized fail\", \"from\": 293, \"to\": 314}, {\"ngram\": \"links\", \"from\": 353, \"to\": 358}, {\"ngram\": \"our site\", \"from\": 362, \"to\": 370}, {\"ngram\": \"an affiliate commission\", \"from\": 384, \"to\": 407}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Every Olympics needs a villain, an omnipresent force that the citizens of the world can come together as one to root against.\", \"from\": 431, \"to\": 556, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Every Olympics\", \"from\": 431, \"to\": 445}, {\"ngram\": \"a villain\", \"from\": 452, \"to\": 461}, {\"ngram\": \"an omnipresent force\", \"from\": 463, \"to\": 483}, {\"ngram\": \"the citizens\", \"from\": 489, \"to\": 501}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 505, \"to\": 514}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And though the 2024 Olympics in Paris are just a few days old as of this writing, a clear contender has emerged in the race to be the undisputed villain of this particular olympiad.\", \"from\": 557, \"to\": 738, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 589, \"end\": 594, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.165171784243203e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Olympics\", \"from\": 568, \"to\": 585}, {\"ngram\": \"this writing\", \"from\": 625, \"to\": 637}, {\"ngram\": \"a clear contender\", \"from\": 639, \"to\": 656}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 672, \"to\": 680}, {\"ngram\": \"the undisputed villain\", \"from\": 687, \"to\": 709}, {\"ngram\": \"this particular olympiad\", \"from\": 713, \"to\": 737}]}, {\"sentence\": \"My fellow Olympics fans, rise to your feet and give a hearty jeer to theGoogle Geminiad, in which a father turns to the AI platform to compose a fan letter to an Olympic sprinter on his daughter's behalf.\", \"from\": 740, \"to\": 944, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"My fellow Olympics fans\", \"from\": 740, \"to\": 763}, {\"ngram\": \"your feet\", \"from\": 773, \"to\": 782}, {\"ngram\": \"a hearty jeer\", \"from\": 792, \"to\": 805}, {\"ngram\": \"theGoogle Geminiad\", \"from\": 809, \"to\": 827}, {\"ngram\": \"a father\", \"from\": 838, \"to\": 846}, {\"ngram\": \"the AI platform\", \"from\": 856, \"to\": 871}, {\"ngram\": \"a fan letter\", \"from\": 883, \"to\": 895}, {\"ngram\": \"an Olympic sprinter\", \"from\": 899, \"to\": 918}, {\"ngram\": \"his daughter's behalf\", \"from\": 922, \"to\": 943}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I have beenwatching the Olympics on Peacock, so I can not speak as to how frequently this ad is being broadcast onNBCor its many other channels.\", \"from\": 946, \"to\": 1090, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 966, \"to\": 978}, {\"ngram\": \"Peacock\", \"from\": 982, \"to\": 989}, {\"ngram\": \"this ad\", \"from\": 1031, \"to\": 1038}, {\"ngram\": \"its many other channels\", \"from\": 1066, \"to\": 1089}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But on the streaming service, the Gemini ad surfaces with the regularity of an Olympic swimmer coming up for air.\", \"from\": 1091, \"to\": 1204, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the streaming service\", \"from\": 1098, \"to\": 1119}, {\"ngram\": \"the regularity\", \"from\": 1149, \"to\": 1163}, {\"ngram\": \"an Olympic swimmer\", \"from\": 1167, \"to\": 1185}, {\"ngram\": \"air\", \"from\": 1200, \"to\": 1203}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And each time the ad appears, my brow furrows, my fist clenches, and my face takes on the dour cast of a Soviet gymnastics judge from back in the day.\", \"from\": 1205, \"to\": 1355, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1310, \"end\": 1316, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soviet_Union\", \"score\": 0.9999998262674277, \"rank\": 1.7371253000569008e-07, \"text\": \"Soviet\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soviet_Union\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soviet_Union\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the ad\", \"from\": 1219, \"to\": 1225}, {\"ngram\": \"my brow\", \"from\": 1235, \"to\": 1242}, {\"ngram\": \"my face\", \"from\": 1274, \"to\": 1281}, {\"ngram\": \"the dour cast\", \"from\": 1291, \"to\": 1304}, {\"ngram\": \"the day\", \"from\": 1347, \"to\": 1354}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Quiet simply, theGoogleGemini ad enrages because it embraces and celebrates the very worst things about AI-powered tools.\", \"from\": 1357, \"to\": 1478, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Quiet\", \"from\": 1357, \"to\": 1362}, {\"ngram\": \"simply, theGoogleGemini ad enrages\", \"from\": 1363, \"to\": 1397}, {\"ngram\": \"the very worst things\", \"from\": 1433, \"to\": 1454}, {\"ngram\": \"AI-powered tools\", \"from\": 1461, \"to\": 1477}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If this is how Google is hoping to sell the capabilities of AI in general and Gemini in particular to a dubious public, it's badly missed the mark.\", \"from\": 1479, \"to\": 1626, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1494, \"end\": 1500, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.4285481808935853e-16, \"text\": \"Google\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\"}, {\"begin\": 1539, \"end\": 1541, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 5.422943902424678e-13, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}, {\"begin\": 1557, \"end\": 1563, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Gemini\", \"score\": 0.869939358640752, \"rank\": 0.14950541100061981, \"text\": \"Gemini\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Gemini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Gemini\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the capabilities\", \"from\": 1519, \"to\": 1535}, {\"ngram\": \"a dubious public\", \"from\": 1581, \"to\": 1597}, {\"ngram\": \"the mark\", \"from\": 1617, \"to\": 1625}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thefull 1-minute spot from Googlestarts out innocently enough.\", \"from\": 1628, \"to\": 1690, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"1-minute spot\", \"from\": 1636, \"to\": 1649}, {\"ngram\": \"Googlestarts\", \"from\": 1655, \"to\": 1667}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A father is telling us about his daughter who's shaping up to be quite the runner - not unlike U.S. Olympian Sydney McLaughlin-Levrone, whose record-breaking exploits are an inspiration to the girl at the heart of the ad.\", \"from\": 1691, \"to\": 1912, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1800, \"end\": 1806, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9999998586913634, \"rank\": 1.4130028874670024e-07, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A father\", \"from\": 1691, \"to\": 1699}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 1711, \"to\": 1713}, {\"ngram\": \"his daughter\", \"from\": 1720, \"to\": 1732}, {\"ngram\": \"quite the runner\", \"from\": 1756, \"to\": 1772}, {\"ngram\": \"whose record-breaking exploits\", \"from\": 1827, \"to\": 1857}, {\"ngram\": \"an inspiration\", \"from\": 1862, \"to\": 1876}, {\"ngram\": \"the girl\", \"from\": 1880, \"to\": 1888}, {\"ngram\": \"the heart\", \"from\": 1892, \"to\": 1901}, {\"ngram\": \"the ad\", \"from\": 1905, \"to\": 1911}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Within 20 seconds, we have seen young children with dreams of glory!\", \"from\": 1913, \"to\": 1981, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"20 seconds\", \"from\": 1920, \"to\": 1930}, {\"ngram\": \"young children\", \"from\": 1945, \"to\": 1959}, {\"ngram\": \"dreams\", \"from\": 1965, \"to\": 1971}, {\"ngram\": \"glory\", \"from\": 1975, \"to\": 1980}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A proud father talking up his little girl!\", \"from\": 1982, \"to\": 2024, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A proud father\", \"from\": 1982, \"to\": 1996}, {\"ngram\": \"his little girl\", \"from\": 2008, \"to\": 2023}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An Olympic medalist back for more!\", \"from\": 2025, \"to\": 2059, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"An Olympic medalist\", \"from\": 2025, \"to\": 2044}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What kind of monster would object to any of this?\", \"from\": 2060, \"to\": 2109, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"What kind\", \"from\": 2060, \"to\": 2069}, {\"ngram\": \"monster\", \"from\": 2073, \"to\": 2080}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I suggest you keep watching.\", \"from\": 2111, \"to\": 2139, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After Googling for tips on hurdling techniques and getting a Gemini-generated summary - a perfectly fine use of search tools, I hasten to add - our dad narrator then veers into shakier territory.\", \"from\": 2141, \"to\": 2336, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"tips\", \"from\": 2160, \"to\": 2164}, {\"ngram\": \"techniques\", \"from\": 2177, \"to\": 2187}, {\"ngram\": \"a Gemini-generated summary\", \"from\": 2200, \"to\": 2226}, {\"ngram\": \"a perfectly fine use\", \"from\": 2229, \"to\": 2249}, {\"ngram\": \"search tools\", \"from\": 2253, \"to\": 2265}, {\"ngram\": \"our dad narrator\", \"from\": 2285, \"to\": 2301}, {\"ngram\": \"shakier territory\", \"from\": 2318, \"to\": 2335}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"She wants to show Sydney some love,\\\" the dad says.\", \"from\": 2337, \"to\": 2388, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2356, \"end\": 2362, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9999998586913634, \"rank\": 1.4130028874670024e-07, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some love\", \"from\": 2363, \"to\": 2372}, {\"ngram\": \"the dad\", \"from\": 2375, \"to\": 2382}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"And I am pretty good with words.\", \"from\": 2389, \"to\": 2422, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"words\", \"from\": 2416, \"to\": 2421}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But this has to be just right.\", \"from\": 2423, \"to\": 2453, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So, Gemini, help my daughter write a letter telling Sydney how inspiring she is.\\\"\", \"from\": 2454, \"to\": 2535, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2458, \"end\": 2464, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Gemini\", \"score\": 0.869939358640752, \"rank\": 0.14950541100061981, \"text\": \"Gemini\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Gemini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Gemini\"}, {\"begin\": 2506, \"end\": 2512, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9999998586913634, \"rank\": 1.4130028874670024e-07, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my daughter\", \"from\": 2471, \"to\": 2482}, {\"ngram\": \"a letter\", \"from\": 2489, \"to\": 2497}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The ad ends with Gemini composing said letter as the words \\\"A little help from Gemini\\\" flash up on the screen.\", \"from\": 2536, \"to\": 2646, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2553, \"end\": 2559, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Gemini\", \"score\": 0.869939358640752, \"rank\": 0.14950541100061981, \"text\": \"Gemini\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Gemini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Gemini\"}, {\"begin\": 2615, \"end\": 2621, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Gemini\", \"score\": 0.869939358640752, \"rank\": 0.14950541100061981, \"text\": \"Gemini\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Gemini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Gemini\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The ad\", \"from\": 2536, \"to\": 2542}, {\"ngram\": \"said letter\", \"from\": 2570, \"to\": 2581}, {\"ngram\": \"the words\", \"from\": 2585, \"to\": 2594}, {\"ngram\": \"A little help\", \"from\": 2596, \"to\": 2609}, {\"ngram\": \"the screen\", \"from\": 2635, \"to\": 2645}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Get instant access to breaking news, the hottest reviews, great deals and helpful tips.\", \"from\": 2648, \"to\": 2735, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"instant access\", \"from\": 2652, \"to\": 2666}, {\"ngram\": \"breaking news\", \"from\": 2670, \"to\": 2683}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Well, more than just a little, one might argue, since it's Gemini coming up with all the wording.\", \"from\": 2737, \"to\": 2834, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2796, \"end\": 2802, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Gemini\", \"score\": 0.869939358640752, \"rank\": 0.14950541100061981, \"text\": \"Gemini\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Gemini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Gemini\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"one\", \"from\": 2768, \"to\": 2771}, {\"ngram\": \"all the wording\", \"from\": 2818, \"to\": 2833}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I have some follow-up questions for Google and/or Gemini: Seriously, there is nothing more personal than a fan letter that expresses how much someone impresses and inspires you.\", \"from\": 2836, \"to\": 3014, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2872, \"end\": 2878, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.4285481808935853e-16, \"text\": \"Google\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some follow-up questions\", \"from\": 2843, \"to\": 2867}, {\"ngram\": \"Gemini\", \"from\": 2886, \"to\": 2892}, {\"ngram\": \"nothing\", \"from\": 2914, \"to\": 2921}, {\"ngram\": \"a fan letter\", \"from\": 2941, \"to\": 2953}, {\"ngram\": \"someone\", \"from\": 2978, \"to\": 2985}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And there is no more impersonal way to compose such a letter than to have a robot do it for you.\", \"from\": 3015, \"to\": 3111, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no more impersonal way\", \"from\": 3028, \"to\": 3050}, {\"ngram\": \"such a letter\", \"from\": 3062, \"to\": 3075}, {\"ngram\": \"a robot\", \"from\": 3089, \"to\": 3096}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As someone who gets a lot of email each day, I can tell you it's really easy to spot which ones are form letters, and I am going to guess that Gemini has not cracked the code on how to make such a letter sound like it's coming from the heart.\", \"from\": 3112, \"to\": 3354, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3255, \"end\": 3261, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Gemini\", \"score\": 0.869939358640752, \"rank\": 0.14950541100061981, \"text\": \"Gemini\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Gemini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Gemini\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"someone\", \"from\": 3115, \"to\": 3122}, {\"ngram\": \"a lot\", \"from\": 3132, \"to\": 3137}, {\"ngram\": \"email\", \"from\": 3141, \"to\": 3146}, {\"ngram\": \"which ones\", \"from\": 3197, \"to\": 3207}, {\"ngram\": \"form letters\", \"from\": 3212, \"to\": 3224}, {\"ngram\": \"the code\", \"from\": 3278, \"to\": 3286}, {\"ngram\": \"such a letter\", \"from\": 3302, \"to\": 3315}, {\"ngram\": \"the heart\", \"from\": 3344, \"to\": 3353}]}, {\"sentence\": \"AI-powered features are finding their way into a lot of products as of late, particularly when it comes to the smartphones I spend a lot of time testing and writing about.\", \"from\": 3358, \"to\": 3529, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"AI-powered features\", \"from\": 3358, \"to\": 3377}, {\"ngram\": \"their way\", \"from\": 3390, \"to\": 3399}, {\"ngram\": \"a lot\", \"from\": 3405, \"to\": 3410}, {\"ngram\": \"products\", \"from\": 3414, \"to\": 3422}, {\"ngram\": \"the smartphones\", \"from\": 3465, \"to\": 3480}, {\"ngram\": \"a lot\", \"from\": 3489, \"to\": 3494}, {\"ngram\": \"time testing\", \"from\": 3498, \"to\": 3510}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So I have spent a good portion of the past year trying out various AI features, which has given me some idea of where the technology thrives and where it stumbles.\", \"from\": 3530, \"to\": 3693, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3597, \"end\": 3599, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 5.422943902424678e-13, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a good portion\", \"from\": 3546, \"to\": 3560}, {\"ngram\": \"the past year\", \"from\": 3564, \"to\": 3577}, {\"ngram\": \"some idea\", \"from\": 3629, \"to\": 3638}, {\"ngram\": \"the technology\", \"from\": 3648, \"to\": 3662}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On the phone at least, the best kind of AI features take dull, labor-intensive tasks off my hands so that I can be freed up to do more creative thinking.\", \"from\": 3695, \"to\": 3848, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3735, \"end\": 3737, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 5.422943902424678e-13, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the phone\", \"from\": 3698, \"to\": 3707}, {\"ngram\": \"the best kind\", \"from\": 3718, \"to\": 3731}, {\"ngram\": \"dull, labor-intensive tasks\", \"from\": 3752, \"to\": 3779}, {\"ngram\": \"my hands\", \"from\": 3784, \"to\": 3792}, {\"ngram\": \"more creative thinking\", \"from\": 3825, \"to\": 3847}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Transcribing an audio recording is a great example of that, as tackling that by yourself means listening to the audio, typing what you hear, rewinding the audio to make sure you did not miss anything, and correcting any typos you have made along the way.\", \"from\": 3849, \"to\": 4103, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an audio recording\", \"from\": 3862, \"to\": 3880}, {\"ngram\": \"a great example\", \"from\": 3884, \"to\": 3899}, {\"ngram\": \"the audio\", \"from\": 3957, \"to\": 3966}, {\"ngram\": \"the audio\", \"from\": 4000, \"to\": 4009}, {\"ngram\": \"anything\", \"from\": 4040, \"to\": 4048}, {\"ngram\": \"any typos\", \"from\": 4065, \"to\": 4074}, {\"ngram\": \"the way\", \"from\": 4095, \"to\": 4102}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is beyond tedious, and it takes a long time, even for a speedy typist.\", \"from\": 4104, \"to\": 4177, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a long time\", \"from\": 4139, \"to\": 4150}, {\"ngram\": \"a speedy typist\", \"from\": 4161, \"to\": 4176}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An AI platform can handle that very quickly, if not always as accurately as I would like to see.\", \"from\": 4178, \"to\": 4274, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4181, \"end\": 4183, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 5.422943902424678e-13, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But still, it's a productivity booster, which is why you will find that feature on Samsung phones, Pixel devices and - onceiOS 18is fully released - iPhones.\", \"from\": 4275, \"to\": 4432, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4358, \"end\": 4365, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samsung\", \"score\": 0.9999999983215275, \"rank\": 1.6779847883968118e-09, \"text\": \"Samsung\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samsung\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samsung\"}, {\"begin\": 4374, \"end\": 4379, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pixel\", \"score\": 0.5690775860112257, \"rank\": 0.7572296371908144, \"text\": \"Pixel\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pixel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pixel\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a productivity booster\", \"from\": 4291, \"to\": 4313}, {\"ngram\": \"that feature\", \"from\": 4342, \"to\": 4354}, {\"ngram\": \"- onceiOS\", \"from\": 4392, \"to\": 4401}, {\"ngram\": \"18is fully released - iPhones\", \"from\": 4402, \"to\": 4431}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I saw another great example of how AI can be put to good use this past spring at Google I/O ina demo of Gemini Advanced.The AI platform was able to analyze two documents - a 522-page PDF and a 144-page one - and identify topics covered in one document but not the other.\", \"from\": 4434, \"to\": 4704, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4469, \"end\": 4471, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 5.422943902424678e-13, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}, {\"begin\": 4538, \"end\": 4544, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Gemini\", \"score\": 0.869939358640752, \"rank\": 0.14950541100061981, \"text\": \"Gemini\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Gemini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Gemini\"}, {\"begin\": 4617, \"end\": 4620, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/PDF\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.105886783260533e-17, \"text\": \"PDF\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/PDF\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/PDF\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"another great example\", \"from\": 4440, \"to\": 4461}, {\"ngram\": \"good use\", \"from\": 4486, \"to\": 4494}, {\"ngram\": \"Google I\", \"from\": 4515, \"to\": 4523}, {\"ngram\": \"O ina demo\", \"from\": 4524, \"to\": 4534}, {\"ngram\": \"The AI platform\", \"from\": 4554, \"to\": 4569}, {\"ngram\": \"two documents\", \"from\": 4590, \"to\": 4603}, {\"ngram\": \"topics\", \"from\": 4655, \"to\": 4661}, {\"ngram\": \"one document\", \"from\": 4673, \"to\": 4685}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That would be a mind-numbing project for a person, but an AI model can handle it with ease.\", \"from\": 4705, \"to\": 4796, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4763, \"end\": 4765, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 5.422943902424678e-13, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a mind-numbing project\", \"from\": 4719, \"to\": 4741}, {\"ngram\": \"a person\", \"from\": 4746, \"to\": 4754}, {\"ngram\": \"ease\", \"from\": 4791, \"to\": 4795}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Where AI tends to stumble in my experience is when you ask it to perform the kinds of personal tasks best handled on your own.\", \"from\": 4798, \"to\": 4924, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"AI\", \"from\": 4804, \"to\": 4806}, {\"ngram\": \"my experience\", \"from\": 4827, \"to\": 4840}, {\"ngram\": \"the kinds\", \"from\": 4871, \"to\": 4880}, {\"ngram\": \"personal tasks\", \"from\": 4884, \"to\": 4898}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is aChat Assist feature in Galaxy AIthat offers to adjust the tone of any text messages you send - when I tested it, the people I texted with were largely able to figure out which messages came from me and which ones had been tweaked by an algorithm.\", \"from\": 4925, \"to\": 5181, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"aChat Assist feature\", \"from\": 4934, \"to\": 4954}, {\"ngram\": \"Galaxy AIthat\", \"from\": 4958, \"to\": 4971}, {\"ngram\": \"the tone\", \"from\": 4989, \"to\": 4997}, {\"ngram\": \"any text messages\", \"from\": 5001, \"to\": 5018}, {\"ngram\": \"the people\", \"from\": 5048, \"to\": 5058}, {\"ngram\": \"which messages\", \"from\": 5105, \"to\": 5119}, {\"ngram\": \"which ones\", \"from\": 5137, \"to\": 5147}, {\"ngram\": \"an algorithm\", \"from\": 5168, \"to\": 5180}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Having an AI fine-tune your texts - or your fan letters to Olympians, for that matter - may tackle any anxiety you have about getting your message across, but it strips you of your humanity in the process.\", \"from\": 5185, \"to\": 5390, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5195, \"end\": 5197, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 5.422943902424678e-13, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"your texts\", \"from\": 5208, \"to\": 5218}, {\"ngram\": \"your fan letters\", \"from\": 5224, \"to\": 5240}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympians\", \"from\": 5244, \"to\": 5253}, {\"ngram\": \"that matter\", \"from\": 5259, \"to\": 5270}, {\"ngram\": \"any anxiety\", \"from\": 5284, \"to\": 5295}, {\"ngram\": \"your message\", \"from\": 5319, \"to\": 5331}, {\"ngram\": \"your humanity\", \"from\": 5361, \"to\": 5374}, {\"ngram\": \"the process\", \"from\": 5378, \"to\": 5389}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I do not think that's something tech companies should be pushing for in their relentless pursuit to cram AI into every function.\", \"from\": 5391, \"to\": 5519, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5496, \"end\": 5498, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 5.422943902424678e-13, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 5413, \"to\": 5422}, {\"ngram\": \"companies\", \"from\": 5428, \"to\": 5437}, {\"ngram\": \"their relentless pursuit\", \"from\": 5463, \"to\": 5487}, {\"ngram\": \"every function\", \"from\": 5504, \"to\": 5518}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And I certainly do not think it's something that should be the cornerstone of a multi-million-dollar ad campaign meant to convince me that AI tools will make my life better.\", \"from\": 5520, \"to\": 5693, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5659, \"end\": 5661, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 5.422943902424678e-13, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 5554, \"to\": 5563}, {\"ngram\": \"the cornerstone\", \"from\": 5579, \"to\": 5594}, {\"ngram\": \"a multi-million-dollar ad campaign\", \"from\": 5598, \"to\": 5632}, {\"ngram\": \"my life\", \"from\": 5678, \"to\": 5685}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Google would beg to differ, at least based ona statement the company gave to CNNin which it contends that \\\"that AI can be a great tool for enhancing human creativity, but can never replace it.\\\"\", \"from\": 5695, \"to\": 5888, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5695, \"end\": 5701, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.4285481808935853e-16, \"text\": \"Google\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\"}, {\"begin\": 5807, \"end\": 5809, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 5.422943902424678e-13, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"at least based ona statement\", \"from\": 5723, \"to\": 5751}, {\"ngram\": \"the company\", \"from\": 5752, \"to\": 5763}, {\"ngram\": \"CNNin\", \"from\": 5772, \"to\": 5777}, {\"ngram\": \"a great tool\", \"from\": 5817, \"to\": 5829}, {\"ngram\": \"human creativity\", \"from\": 5844, \"to\": 5860}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The statement goes on to say that ad \\\"aims to show how the Gemini app can provide a starting point, thought starter, or early draft for someone looking for ideas for their writing.\\\"\", \"from\": 5890, \"to\": 6071, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5949, \"end\": 5955, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Gemini\", \"score\": 0.869939358640752, \"rank\": 0.14950541100061981, \"text\": \"Gemini\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Gemini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Gemini\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The statement\", \"from\": 5890, \"to\": 5903}, {\"ngram\": \"ad\", \"from\": 5924, \"to\": 5926}, {\"ngram\": \"a starting point\", \"from\": 5972, \"to\": 5988}, {\"ngram\": \"starter\", \"from\": 5998, \"to\": 6005}, {\"ngram\": \"early draft\", \"from\": 6010, \"to\": 6021}, {\"ngram\": \"someone\", \"from\": 6026, \"to\": 6033}, {\"ngram\": \"ideas\", \"from\": 6046, \"to\": 6051}, {\"ngram\": \"their writing\", \"from\": 6056, \"to\": 6069}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Which would be a fine counter-argument if, at any point, we saw someone creating something in the ad.\", \"from\": 6072, \"to\": 6173, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a fine counter\", \"from\": 6087, \"to\": 6101}, {\"ngram\": \"argument\", \"from\": 6102, \"to\": 6110}, {\"ngram\": \"any point\", \"from\": 6118, \"to\": 6127}, {\"ngram\": \"someone\", \"from\": 6136, \"to\": 6143}, {\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 6153, \"to\": 6162}, {\"ngram\": \"the ad\", \"from\": 6166, \"to\": 6172}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All we ever see is Gemini spitting out text.\", \"from\": 6174, \"to\": 6218, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6193, \"end\": 6199, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Gemini\", \"score\": 0.869939358640752, \"rank\": 0.14950541100061981, \"text\": \"Gemini\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Gemini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Gemini\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"text\", \"from\": 6213, \"to\": 6217}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So yeah, not a very good ad.\", \"from\": 6220, \"to\": 6248, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"So yeah, not a very good ad\", \"from\": 6220, \"to\": 6247}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hopefully, it gets Google to rethink just what it's trying to say about AI and how it goes about saying it.\", \"from\": 6249, \"to\": 6356, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6268, \"end\": 6274, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.4285481808935853e-16, \"text\": \"Google\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\"}, {\"begin\": 6321, \"end\": 6323, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 5.422943902424678e-13, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And the next time Google looks to convince people that these tools are about sparking creativity and not superseding it, maybe try doing it without Gemini's input first.\", \"from\": 6357, \"to\": 6526, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6375, \"end\": 6381, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.4285481808935853e-16, \"text\": \"Google\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\"}, {\"begin\": 6505, \"end\": 6511, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Gemini\", \"score\": 0.869939358640752, \"rank\": 0.14950541100061981, \"text\": \"Gemini\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Gemini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Gemini\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 6400, \"to\": 6406}, {\"ngram\": \"these tools\", \"from\": 6412, \"to\": 6423}, {\"ngram\": \"creativity\", \"from\": 6443, \"to\": 6453}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Philip Michaels is a Managing Editor at Tom's Guide.\", \"from\": 6528, \"to\": 6580, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Philip Michaels\", \"from\": 6528, \"to\": 6543}, {\"ngram\": \"a Managing Editor\", \"from\": 6547, \"to\": 6564}, {\"ngram\": \"Tom's Guide\", \"from\": 6568, \"to\": 6579}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He's been covering personal technology since 1999 and was in the building when Steve Jobs showed off the iPhone for the first time.\", \"from\": 6581, \"to\": 6712, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6660, \"end\": 6670, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_Jobs\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.091720307031954e-56, \"text\": \"Steve Jobs\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_Jobs\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_Jobs\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"personal technology\", \"from\": 6600, \"to\": 6619}, {\"ngram\": \"the building\", \"from\": 6642, \"to\": 6654}, {\"ngram\": \"the iPhone\", \"from\": 6682, \"to\": 6692}, {\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 6697, \"to\": 6711}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He's been evaluating smartphones since that first iPhone debuted in 2007, and he's been following phone carriers and smartphone plans since 2015.\", \"from\": 6713, \"to\": 6858, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"smartphones\", \"from\": 6734, \"to\": 6745}, {\"ngram\": \"that first iPhone\", \"from\": 6752, \"to\": 6769}, {\"ngram\": \"phone carriers\", \"from\": 6811, \"to\": 6825}, {\"ngram\": \"smartphone plans\", \"from\": 6830, \"to\": 6846}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He has strong opinions about Apple, the Oakland Athletics, old movies and proper butchery techniques.\", \"from\": 6859, \"to\": 6960, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6888, \"end\": 6893, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0700987902709997e-23, \"text\": \"Apple\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\"}, {\"begin\": 6899, \"end\": 6916, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oakland_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.9998548493461095, \"rank\": 0.00014517172551710455, \"text\": \"Oakland Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oakland_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oakland_Athletics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"strong opinions\", \"from\": 6866, \"to\": 6881}, {\"ngram\": \"old movies\", \"from\": 6918, \"to\": 6928}, {\"ngram\": \"proper butchery techniques\", \"from\": 6933, \"to\": 6959}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow him at @PhilipMichaels.\", \"from\": 6961, \"to\": 6991, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"@PhilipMichaels\", \"from\": 6975, \"to\": 6990}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tom's Guide is part of Future US Inc, an international media group and leading digital publisher.Visit our corporate site.\", \"from\": 6993, \"to\": 7115, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7016, \"end\": 7025, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Future_US\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Future US\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid